Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Meanwhile, drain the @sweetcorn{160%g} in a #sieve{}.

Pour the @water{240%ml}(for the couscous) and half the @chicken stock paste{20%g} into a #saucepan{}. Bring to the boil.

Remove from the heat, stir in the @couscous{120%g} and cover. Leave to the side, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{1%pack} and sweetcorn. Fry, ~{5-6%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. 
> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Next, stir in the @tomato puree{30%g}, @chipotle paste{20%g} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), remaining chicken stock paste, @water{125%ml}(for the sauce) and @sugar{1/2%tsp}(for the sauce).

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat. Simmer, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Remove from the heat. Stir in the @BBQ sauce{48%g} and @butter{20%g}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Share the couscous and chicken stew between #bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the @crispy onions{1%sachet}.

Enjoy!